tr.td: Ketogenic foods help to recover from cancer ( Onyeaghala et al., 2015)
A flavonoid with antioxidant and antifungal activity to inhibit growth or spore germination ( Čechovská et al., 2011)
A monoterpene ketone and an essential oil

Precursor to organic acid synthesis; glycine betaine is an osmoprotectant/compatible solute, i.e., a substance highly soluble in water, which protects the proteins from denaturation and enhances plant tolerance to abiotic stress ( Sakamoto and Murata, 2002)
Trichloroacetic acid, hexadecyl ester or Hexadecyltrichloroacetate
Acetic acid, hydroxy-, methyl ester or methyl glycolate
Glycolate is a part of primary plant metabolism and photosynthesis ( Cui et al., 2016)
anti-inflammatory, antiandrogenic, and anemiagenic properties ( Surender et al., 2008)
9,12,15-Octadecatrienoic acid, methyl ester, (Z,Z,Z)- or methyl linolenate
Anticancer and cytotoxic ( Krishnan et al., 2014)
Octadecanoic acid, methyl ester or methyl stearate
Natural Preservative against bacterial food spoilage ( Arokiyaraj et al., 2018)
Benzoic acid, 2-hydroxy-, 3-methyl butyl ester or isoamyl salicylate
Hexadecanoic acid, methyl ester or methyl palmitate
Herbicide with antifungal properties ( Martelloni et al., 2020) (US patent 5,683,962)
Major anti-algal chemical ( Choe and Jung, 2002) ( Choi and Jiang, 2014)
Antioxidant and antiproliferative activities ( Zhou et al., 2008)
Antioxidant and antiproliferative activities ( Zhou et al., 2008)
Flavoring agent, nutraceutical (has use in cosmetics) Gunia-Krzyżak et al., 2018
Analgesic, anticancer, anti-inflammatory and anti-diarrhoeal ( Farooq et al., 2019)
Terpenoid or hemiterpene alcohol compound with different physiological roles ( Pandey et al., 2019)
Smoky flavor nutraceutical antioxidant ( Loo et al., 2008)
Allelochemical and natural germination inhibitor ( Darabi et al., 2007)
Larvicides against malaria, dengue and filariasis mosquitoes ( Govindarajan et al., 2016)
Antibacterial, antioxidant ( Mishra and Sree, 2007) and anticancer ( Lee et al., 2007)
Anticancer, antimicrobial and antioxidant ( Manoj et al., 2012)
Anticancer, antimicrobial and antioxidant ( Manoj et al., 2012)
Floral essential oil precursor to laurolactam, a precursor to the polymer Nylon-12. Antioxidant, toxic to brine shrimp larvae ( Salehi et al., 2019)
Strong defensing activity against a number of pathogens, antifungal and antibacterial ( Biswas et al., 2017)
Insecticidal and antifungal ( Manoj et al., 2012)
Natural wax of plants, a semiochemical, contact and volatile pheromone ( Nerio et al., 2010)
Highly repellant to insects ( Nerio et al., 2010)
Antibacterial and antifungal ( Mahmood et al., 2009)
Herbicide and antibacterial ( Kini et al., 2010)
Antibacterial, antifungal, antiviral, analgesics, anti-inflammatory, antitumor, antitubarcular, antimalarial and anti-diabetic ( Choudhary et al., 2018)
Present in many plants but biological function not determined
Antibiotic, larvicidal and repellent Activity ( Sivakumar et al., 2011)
Anti-stress role, precursor of antimicrobial and other bioactive molecules ( Salehi et al., 2019)
Important long chain fatty acid, role in plant defense against pathogens ( Coleman and Hudson, 2016)
Plant defense, antimicrobial, anti- inflammatory, hypocholesterolemic and hepatoprotective

Anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, Hypocholesterolemic nematicide, pesticide, antiandrogenic flavor and hemolytic ( Aparna et al., 2012), 5-Alpha reductase inhibitor and potent mosquito; larvicide ( Carta et al., 2017; Rahuman et al., 2000, 2009), anti-inflammatory ( Vasudevan et al., 2012)
Relieves stress, particularly salinity stress ( Sahebi et al., 2015)
